Class SeleniumWrapper

java.lang.Object
  org.aludratest.service.gui.web.selenium.selenium1.SeleniumWrapper

public class SeleniumWrapper
extends Object

Wraps an instance of the SeleniumFacade and provides methods for accessing UI elements and timing.

Author:
Marcel Malitz, Joerg Langnickel, Volker Bergmann

retryUntilTimeout

public boolean retryUntilTimeout(ConditionCheck condition)
Retries to evaluate the condition. If evaluation is successful, the method will return regularly. If not, this method will retry it with a pause of SeleniumWrapperConfiguration.getPauseBetweenRetries() ms between retries until a timeout of SeleniumWrapperConfiguration.getTimeout() ms is exceeded.

Parameters:
condition - which will be evaluated on each retry
Returns:
true, if the condition could be executed successfully; otherwise false will be returned.
